# ============================================================
# Global git excludes — installed to ~/.gitignore_global and
# wired up via:  git config --global core.excludesfile ~/.gitignore_global
#
# Applies to EVERY repo on this machine without per-project setup.
# Keep this tight: only generated working artifacts that should
# never be committed. Do NOT add broad rules (e.g. *.md, docs/)
# here — they would hide legitimate project documentation.
# ============================================================

# --- Claude workflow: generated plan/spec working docs ---
# brainstorming -> docs/superpowers/specs/<date>-<topic>-design.md
# writing-plans -> docs/superpowers/plans/<date>-<feature>.md
# These are local thinking artifacts, not shippable source.
docs/superpowers/plans/
docs/superpowers/specs/
**/docs/superpowers/plans/
**/docs/superpowers/specs/
